sory guidance while considering the action context to avoid conflicts.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Validating Native Image Setup**\\n\\nIt seems like the Native Image verification is necessary, and I might find that the jrt build argument is already included in the current scaffold if it's copied from a previous version. There's also a note that dynamic runtime compilation within a native image could reveal limitations in reachability, which is important to consider. Also, if I'm using the optional Ant adapter, it requires Ant to be covered. Finally, I just need the final JSON.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Janino 3.1.0 does not need an extra Maven dependency or Docker service; the compile failure comes from a stale import after iterator utilities moved to commons-compiler, which janino already resolves transitively. Meaningful native-image coverage should preserve Janino's JDK class/resource access setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For Janino 3.1.x tests, do not import org.codehaus.janino.util.iterator.*; use org.codehaus.commons.compiler.util.iterator.* if iterator utilities are still exercised. When tests exercise SimpleCompiler, Compiler, ExpressionEvaluator, ScriptEvaluator, or ClassBodyEvaluator against JDK classes in native image, keep/add the native-image test build argument --enable-url-protocols=jrt so Janino can inspect JDK module resources.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"If generated tests deliberately cover org.codehaus.janino.AntCompilerAdapter, the optional/provided Ant API is not brought in transitively and would require a separate dependency, but normal Janino compiler/evaluator coverage should avoid that path.\",\n    \"Runtime Java compilation and class loading remain sensitive in native image; local Gradle and Native Image verification are authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_007ba0ec52e5d5f2016a42755a40348197a